homepage pilot: new taglines, calm matrix base, softer fractures

Taglines (hero rotation):
- "The human in human-in-the-loop."
- "Builds with AI. Argues with AI. Ships anyway."
- "One human, several agents, a vision."
- "Human conductor. Agentic orchestra."
Dropped "Builds with AI. / Ships to production. / Multi-agent.
Multi-tenant. / Senior dev for hire." — the new set carries the
same ideas with more voice. Bumped h1 min-height to reserve room
for the longer phrases so the layout doesn't shift.

Calm matrix base (CSS-only):
- New `.mission-bg.matrix-bg` class: dark navy floor + faint green
  radial halos top/bottom + 1px horizontal scan lines + 26px
  vertical column grid. Zero JS, zero performance cost, matrix
  identity woven into the floor of the page.
- Homepage pilot: kept hero + Active Projects + OpenCare Feature
  as cinematic video anchors. Swapped "What I Build", "Let's Build
  Something", and "Builds — Live Now" from video backgrounds to
  the matrix base. Net: 6 videos -> 3 videos, a lot less noise,
  and the matrix is the resting state instead of black.
- If this pilot lands, the same treatment will roll across the
  rest of the site (websites, ai-apps, the-stack, etc.).

Fracture tweaks — "did I see that?" subtlety:
- Slower rain fall (drops[] increments by 0.32–0.4 instead of 1),
  so characters no longer scroll past too fast to read.
- Shorter holds: LINGER 650–1450ms (was 1400–3200), HARD FLASH
  140–280ms (was 220–440), STUTTER 50–130ms per flash.
- Lower peak opacity: LINGER 0.48–0.56, HARD FLASH 0.62, STUTTER
  0.55 (were all 0.85–1.0). Now feels like a glimpse rather than
  a statement.
